description: Works to trees covered by ENFIELD ORDER NO. 2 (1957)- 2x lime(T8,T31):cut ivy and strip to 2m, 3x lime(T19,T22,T27): remove epicormic growth to a height of 2m, 2x scots pine(T21,T35): fell, (TG6) Mixed Species Group. 3x Lime: remove epicormic growth to a height of 3m, 1x ash: sever ivy and 1x sycamore: fell, 4x lime(TG12): remove epicormic growth to a height of 3m and strip any ivy and 1x oak(T23): undertake Assessment of potential internal decay by mechanical apparatus eg. Resistograph.
